DROP:
  The PostgreSQL DROP TABLE statement is used to remove a table definition and all associated data, indexes, rules, triggers, and constraints for that table. 
  DROP will destroy the whole structure of the table.
  
Syntax:
  ALTER TABLE table_name DROP COLUMN column_name;
  DROP TABLE table_name;
  
Example:
  ALTER TABLE table_name DROP COLUMN id;
  DROP TABLE employee_details;
  
  For documentation of DROP clause refer at https://www.postgresql.org/docs/8.1/sql-droptable.html.
